                    <p class="mb-4">
                        1. <b>Workforce Planning:</b> Assess the organization’s current and future workforce requirements aligned with strategic objectives. Identify the skills, knowledge, and competencies needed for various positions.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mb-4">
                        2. <b>Recruitment Planning:</b> Develop a recruitment strategy outlining methods, resources, and timelines for attracting suitable candidates. Determine the channels for sourcing candidates, such as job boards, social media, employee referrals, or recruitment agencies.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mb-4">
                        3. <b>Candidate Sourcing:</b> Actively search for and attract potential candidates through the identified channels. Source candidates both internally (within the organization) and externally to ensure a diverse and qualified applicant pool.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mb-4">
                        4. <b>Screening and Selection:</b> Review resumes, applications, and cover letters to shortlist candidates who meet the job criteria. Conduct initial screenings, such as phone interviews or online assessments, to evaluate candidates' qualifications and suitability.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mb-4">
                        5. <b>Interview and Evaluation:</b> Conduct structured interviews focusing on behavioral, situational, and technical questions to assess candidate fit. Evaluate candidates against predetermined criteria, gathering feedback from all stakeholders involved in the hiring process.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mb-4">
                        6. <b>Background Checks and References:</b> Verify candidates’ employment history, educational credentials, certifications, and other relevant background details. Contact references to obtain insights into candidates' past performance, work ethic, and suitability.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mb-4">
                        7. <b>Offer and Negotiation:</b> Extend job offers to selected candidates, detailing compensation, benefits, start date, and other relevant terms. Engage in negotiations on salary, benefits, and other aspects of the offer to reach mutually agreeable terms.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mb-4">
                        8. <b>Onboarding and Orientation:</b> Integrate new employees into the organization by providing essential information, resources, and support. Conduct orientation sessions to familiarize them with the organization’s culture, policies, procedures, and expectations.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mb-4">
                        9. <b>Training and Development:</b> Offer ongoing training and development programs to enhance employees' skills and competencies. Provide mentorship, coaching, and other learning opportunities to support professional growth and career advancement.
                    </p>
